<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 3:19AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Hansford and central Ochiltree Counties through 345 AM CDT...
At 318 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southeast of Waka, or 11 miles east of Spearman, moving
northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Perryton, Waka and Farnsworth.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Oklahoma.</instruction>
